Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
You need to take care of the traffic lights. There are three colors of lights on a traffic light. If the red light is on, you need to wait until the red light is off and the green light is on. When the green light start to be off, first the yellow light will be on, then the red light will be on. In this case you should not cross the road.